 helper class may be fine due to automatic test class metadata, but perhaps it’s safer to rely on a JDK or library class with known public constructors. Native image reflection needs metadata for application classes too, but I think the test harness might auto-register test code. I'll keep my focus on the active class.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test configurations**\\n\\nI’m weighing whether to include metadata. Tests need to run under a native image without guards, but a lack of metadata for class constructors might cause issues at runtime. The harness might be utilizing a tracing agent or TCK plugin to generate configurations. I notice existing tests use reflection in helper classes, and they seem to run fine in native tests. I think our helper class approach is okay, but maybe I should write a file to confirm.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FfXgoCehrH55XkDjOVcPefdT|fc_00f4ec312b4d188a0169f0a932c8b081a28231e0a404851605", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/13-ea/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/ConstructorUtilTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_openjfx.javafx_base;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.sun.javafx.reflect.ConstructorUtil;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Constructor;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ConstructorUtilTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void getConstructorFindsMatchingPublicConstructor() throws Exception {\n        Constructor<?> constructor = ConstructorUtil.getConstructor(\n                ConstructorUtilSample.class,\n                new Class<?>[] {String.class, int.class});\n\n        assertThat(constructor.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(ConstructorUtilSample.class);\n        assertThat(constructor.getParameterTypes()).containsExactly(String.class, int.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void getConstructorsReturnsAllPublicConstructors() {\n        Constructor<?>[] constructors = ConstructorUtil.getConstructors(ConstructorUtilSample.class);\n\n        List<List<Class<?>>> parameterTypes = Arrays.stream(constructors)\n                .map(Constructor::getParameterTypes)\n                .map(Arrays::asList)\n                .toList();\n\n        assertThat(parameterTypes)\n                .containsExactlyInAnyOrder(\n                        List.of(),\n                        List.of(String.class),\n                        List.of(String.class, int.class));\n    }\n}\n\nfinal class ConstructorUtilSample {\n\n    public ConstructorUtilSample() {}\n\n    public ConstructorUtilSample(String name) {}\n\n    public ConstructorUtilSample(String name, int priority) {}\n\n    ConstructorUtilSample(int hidden) {}\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.4", "usage": {"input": 149, "output": 1088, "cacheRead": 36480, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37717, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777379620850, "responseId": "resp_00f4ec312b4d188a0169f0a9254e2881a2a28518d9f84e0e4a"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_FfXgoCehrH55XkDjOVcPefdT|fc_00f4ec312b4d188a0169f0a932c8b081a28231e0a404851605", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1777 bytes to tests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/13-ea/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/ConstructorUtilTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777379636425}]}
